Structs/ElsevierHeader.html#/s:11Elsevie.name: accept
Structs/ElsevierHeader.html#/s:11Elsevie.abstract: This represents the acceptable mime types in which the response can be generated. This can also be submitted as the query string parameter httpAccept. Currently, only JSON format responses are supported.

Structs/ElsevierHeader.html#/s:11Elsevie.name: authorization
Structs/ElsevierHeader.html#/s:11Elsevie.abstract: This header field contains the OAuth bearer access token in which the format of the field is Bearer (where the token represents the end-user session key). The presence of a bearer token implies the request will be executed against user-based entitlements. The Authorization field overrides X-ELS-Authtoken.

Structs/ElsevierHeader.html#/s:11Elsevie.name: apiKey
Structs/ElsevierHeader.html#/s:11Elsevie.abstract: This represents a unique application developer key providing access to API resources. This key can also be submitted as the query string parameter apiKey

Structs/ElsevierHeader.html#/s:11Elsevie.name: authToken
Structs/ElsevierHeader.html#/s:11Elsevie.abstract: This represents a end-user session. If provided, this token is used to validate the credentials needed to access content in this resource. This token can also be submitted through the HTTP header Authorization or the query string parameter access_token.

Structs/ElsevierHeader.html#/s:11Elsevie.name: institutionToken
Structs/ElsevierHeader.html#/s:11Elsevie.abstract: This represents a institution token. If provided, this key (in combination with its associated APIKey) is used to establish the credentials needed to access content in this resource. This token can also be provided through the query string parameter insttoken.

Structs/ElsevierHeader.html#/s:11Elsevie.name: requestID
Structs/ElsevierHeader.html#/s:11Elsevie.abstract: This is a client-defined request identifier, which will be logged in all trace messages of the service. This identifier can be used to track a specific transaction in the service’s message logs. It will also be returned as an HTTP header in the corresponding response. Note that this should be a unique identifier for the client, and used to track a single transaction.

Structs/ElsevierHeader.html#/s:11Elsevie.name: resourceVersion
Structs/ElsevierHeader.html#/s:11Elsevie.abstract: Represents the version of the resource that should be received. Multiple attributes can

Enums/ResourceVersionType.html#/s:11Else.name: facetexpand
Enums/ResourceVersionType.html#/s:11Else.abstract: adds new fields under each facet returned (where applicable)

Enums/ResourceVersionType.html#/s:11Else.name: new
Enums/ResourceVersionType.html#/s:11Else.abstract: returns the most recent and prototyped features

Enums/ContentType.html.name: ContentType
Enums/ContentType.html.abstract: This parameter is used to filter specific categories of content that should be searched/returned.

Enums/EVSortDirectionType.html.name: EVSortDirectionType
Enums/EVSortDirectionType.html.abstract: Sort direction. Default setting is dw if parameter is not provided

Enums/EVSortFieldType.html.name: EVSortFieldType
Enums/EVSortFieldType.html.abstract: Sort Field, which can vary by database. Default setting is relevance if parameter is not provided. See here for more information.

Enums/PlatformType.html.name: PlatformType
Enums/PlatformType.html.abstract: Indicates the application platform that should be authenticated; default: scienceDirect

Enums/ResourceVersionType.html.name: ResourceVersionType
Enums/ResourceVersionType.html.abstract: Represents the version of the resource that should be received. Multiple attributes can

Enums/SCAbstractRetrievalViewType.html.name: SCAbstractRetrievalViewType
Enums/SCAbstractRetrievalViewType.html.abstract: This alias represents the list of elements that will be returned in the response.

Enums/SCSearchViewType.html.name: SCSearchViewType
Enums/SCSearchViewType.html.abstract: This alias represents the list of elements that will be returned in the response.

Enums/SCSortType.html.name: SCSortType
Enums/SCSortType.html.abstract: Represents the sort field name and order. A plus in front of the sort field name indicates ascending order, a minus indicates descending order. If sort order is not specified (i.e. no + or -) then the order defaults to ascending (ASC).

Enums/SDArticleEntitlementViewType.html.name: SDArticleEntitlementViewType
Enums/SDArticleEntitlementViewType.html.abstract: This alias represents the list of elements that will be returned in the response.

Enums/SDArticleViewType.html.name: SDArticleViewType
Enums/SDArticleViewType.html.abstract: This alias represents the list of elements that will be returned in the response.

Enums/SDSortType.html.name: SDSortType
Enums/SDSortType.html.abstract: How results should be sorted. Default: relevance.

Enums/SubjectType.html.name: SubjectType
Enums/SubjectType.html.abstract: Represents the subject area code associated with the content category desired. Note that these subject code mapping vary based upon the environment in which the request is executed.

Classes/ElsevierKitScopus.html#/s:11Else.name: affiliation(query:viewType:field:isSuppressNavLinks:start:count:sortTypes:cursor:facets:success:failure:)
Classes/ElsevierKitScopus.html#/s:11Else.abstract: Affiliation Search API: This represents a search against the Affiliation cluster, which contains SCOPUS Affiliation Profiles.

Classes/ElsevierKitScopus.html#/s:11Else.name: author(query:coAuthor:viewType:field:isSuppressNavLinks:start:count:sortTypes:cursor:facets:isAlias:success:failure:)
Classes/ElsevierKitScopus.html#/s:11Else.abstract: Author Search API: This represents a search against the Author cluster, which contains SCOPUS Author Profiles.

Classes/ElsevierKitScopus.html#/s:11Else.name: search(query:viewType:field:isSuppressNavLinks:date:start:count:sortTypes:contentType:subjectType:isAlias:cursor:facets:success:failure:)
Classes/ElsevierKitScopus.html#/s:11Else.abstract: SCOPUS Search API: This represents a search against the SCOPUS cluster, which contains SCOPUS abstracts. Scopus is the largest abstract and citation database of research literature and quality web sources. Updated daily, Scopus covers 50 million abstracts of over 20,500 peer-reviewed titles from more than 5,000 publishers. This search resource allows for the submission of Boolean queries into the Scopus index, retrieving relevant result metadata in a user-specific text formats.

Classes/ElsevierKitScopus.html#/s:11Else.name: abstruct(scopusID:field:viewType:startref:refcount:success:failure:)
Classes/ElsevierKitScopus.html#/s:11Else.abstract: Abstract Retrieval API: This represents retrieval of a SCOPUS abstract by Scopus ID. Each abstract is assigned a unique Scopus identifier (which is also used to create the electronic identifier).

Classes/ElsevierKitScopus.html#/s:11Else.name: abstruct(eid:field:viewType:startref:refcount:success:failure:)
Classes/ElsevierKitScopus.html#/s:11Else.abstract: Abstract Retrieval API: This represents retrieval of a SCOPUS abstract by EID (Electronic Identifier). Each abstract is assigned a unique Scopus identifier which is also used to create the electronic identifier.

Classes/ElsevierKitScopus.html#/s:11Else.name: abstruct(doi:field:viewType:startref:refcount:success:failure:)
Classes/ElsevierKitScopus.html#/s:11Else.abstract: Abstract Retrieval API: This represents retrieval of a SCOPUS abstract by DOI (Document Object Identifier). Note that not every abstract contains a DOI. If only a DOI is available and it cannot be found using this resource, it may still be found by running a Boolean search against the SCIDIR Search API index and using the abstract link (if returned) in those search results.

Classes/ElsevierKitScopus.html#/s:11Else.name: abstruct(pii:field:viewType:startref:refcount:success:failure:)
Classes/ElsevierKitScopus.html#/s:11Else.abstract: Abstract Retrieval API: This represents retrieval of a SCOPUS abstract by PII (Publication Item Identifier). Note that not every abstract contains a PII. If only a PII is available and it cannot be found using this resource, it may still be found by running a Boolean search against the SCIDIR Search API index and using the abstract link (if returned) in those search results.

Classes/ElsevierKitScopus.html#/s:11Else.name: abstruct(pubmedID:field:viewType:startref:refcount:success:failure:)
Classes/ElsevierKitScopus.html#/s:11Else.abstract: Abstract Retrieval API: This represents retrieval of a SCOPUS abstract by MEDLINE ID.

Classes/ElsevierKitScopus.html#/s:11Else.name: abstruct(pui:field:viewType:startref:refcount:success:failure:)
Classes/ElsevierKitScopus.html#/s:11Else.abstract: Abstract Retrieval API: This represents retrieval of a SCOPUS abstract by PUI.

Classes/ElsevierKitScienceDirect.html#/s.name: search(authors:date:isHighlights:offset:show:sortBy:isOpenAccess:issue:loadedAfter:page:pub:qs:title:volume:success:failure:)
Classes/ElsevierKitScienceDirect.html#/s.abstract: ScienceDirect Search API: This represents a search against the ScienceDirect cluster, which contains serial/nonserial full-text articles. ScienceDirect is a leading full-text scientific database offering journal articles and book chapters from more than 2,500 journals and almost 20,000 books. This API resource allows for the submission of Boolean queries into the ScienceDirect index, retrieving relevant result metadata in user-specific text formats.

Classes/ElsevierKitScienceDirect.html#/s.name: article(doi:field:viewType:startref:refcount:success:failure:)
Classes/ElsevierKitScienceDirect.html#/s.abstract: Article Retrieval API: This represents retrieval of a full text article by DOI (Document Object Identifier).

Classes/ElsevierKitScienceDirect.html#/s.name: article(pii:field:viewType:startref:refcount:success:failure:)
Classes/ElsevierKitScienceDirect.html#/s.abstract: Article Retrieval API: This represents retrieval of a full text article by PII (Publication Item Identifier).

Classes/ElsevierKitScienceDirect.html#/s.name: article(eid:field:viewType:startref:refcount:success:failure:)
Classes/ElsevierKitScienceDirect.html#/s.abstract: Article Retrieval API: This represents retrieval of a full text article by EID (Electronic Identifier). This can either be the full-text article identifier or the corresponding Scopus abstract identifier.

Classes/ElsevierKitScienceDirect.html#/s.name: article(scopusID:field:viewType:startref:refcount:success:failure:)
Classes/ElsevierKitScienceDirect.html#/s.abstract: Article Retrieval API: This represents retrieval of a full text article by Scopus ID.

Classes/ElsevierKitScienceDirect.html#/s.name: article(pubmedID:field:viewType:startref:refcount:success:failure:)
Classes/ElsevierKitScienceDirect.html#/s.abstract: Article Retrieval API: This represents retrieval of a full text article by Pubmed ID (Medline ID).

Classes/ElsevierKitScienceDirect.html#/s.name: articleEntitlement(pii:field:viewType:success:failure:)
Classes/ElsevierKitScienceDirect.html#/s.abstract: Full Text Entitlement API: This represents the entitlement status of the full text article(s) specified by PII (Publication Item Identifier). Multiple PII values can be submitted by including them as a comma-delimited list.

Classes/ElsevierKitScienceDirect.html#/s.name: articleEntitlement(doi:field:viewType:success:failure:)
Classes/ElsevierKitScienceDirect.html#/s.abstract: Full Text Entitlement API: This represents the entitlement status of the full text article(s) specified by DOI (Document Object Identifier). Multiple DOI values can be submitted by including them as a comma-delimited list.

Classes/ElsevierKitScienceDirect.html#/s.name: articleEntitlement(eid:field:viewType:success:failure:)
Classes/ElsevierKitScienceDirect.html#/s.abstract: Full Text Entitlement API: This represents the entitlement status of the full text article(s) specified by EID (Electronic Identifier). Multiple EID values can be submitted by including them as a comma-delimited list.

Classes/ElsevierKitScienceDirect.html#/s.name: articleEntitlement(scopusID:field:viewType:success:failure:)
Classes/ElsevierKitScienceDirect.html#/s.abstract: Full Text Entitlement API: This represents the entitlement status of the full text article(s) specified by Scopus ID. Multiple Scopus ID values can be submitted by including them as a comma-delimited list.

Classes/ElsevierKitScienceDirect.html#/s.name: articleEntitlement(pubmedID:field:viewType:success:failure:)
Classes/ElsevierKitScienceDirect.html#/s.abstract: Full Text Entitlement API: This represents the entitlement status of the full text article(s) specified by Pubmed ID (MEDLINE Identifier). Multiple Pubmed ID values can be submitted by including them as a comma-delimited list.
